WEBVTT

00:01.319 --> 00:03.679
All right, everybody.
Great season of softball,

00:03.808 --> 00:05.143
I'm super proud of you, guys.

00:05.267 --> 00:06.827
And I think you're gonna like this

00:06.967 --> 00:08.914
little highlight reel
that I've put together.

00:09.594 --> 00:11.285
Dunder Mifflin!

00:11.535 --> 00:12.840
Andy Bernard presents...

00:12.964 --> 00:15.284
Summer Softball, epic fails!

00:16.170 --> 00:18.305
[Fart] Fail.

00:18.307 --> 00:19.739
[Fart] Fail.

00:19.741 --> 00:21.374
- That's me.
- [Fart] Fail.

00:21.376 --> 00:23.076
Is this like a blooper reel?

00:23.078 --> 00:25.679
A blooper reel?
What is this, 2005?

00:25.681 --> 00:27.581
Do I look like Bob Saget?

00:27.583 --> 00:29.849
Fail!

00:29.851 --> 00:32.052
Who's this guy?

00:32.054 --> 00:34.054
♪ Meow, meow, meow, meow
meow, meow, meow, meow ♪

00:34.055 --> 00:35.655
Look at him dance.
Fail!

00:35.657 --> 00:36.690
Fail.

00:36.692 --> 00:38.325
I deserve that.

00:38.327 --> 00:40.860
♪ Doont-de-doont-de-doont,
doont-de-doont-de-doont ♪

00:40.862 --> 00:42.229
That was a triple.

00:42.231 --> 00:44.998
Can't take the fail?
Get out of the fail video!

00:45.000 --> 00:45.999
My pleasure.

00:46.001 --> 00:47.734
[High-pitched]
Hi, I'm Pete.

00:47.736 --> 00:50.036
Puberty is such a drag, man.

00:50.038 --> 00:53.373
And I'm Clark.
I like to eat toilet paper.

00:53.375 --> 00:55.008
We fail.

00:56.477 --> 00:59.079
I'd like to take a solemn moment
to remember Jerry,

00:59.081 --> 01:01.348
in the warehouse,
who passed away this year.

01:01.350 --> 01:04.450
[Farting]

01:06.354 --> 01:08.288
Well, that's all, folks.

01:08.290 --> 01:10.223
Ski you later, everybody.

01:10.225 --> 01:11.925
Thanks for a great season.

01:11.927 --> 01:13.760
What was that?

01:13.762 --> 01:16.563
That was just normal video
with you making vulgar noises.

01:16.565 --> 01:18.431
Well, I worked with what I had, Oscar.

01:18.433 --> 01:22.535
Next time,
do more fail-ier stuff, okay?

01:22.537 --> 01:24.097
What happened to that video I sent you?

01:24.098 --> 01:26.039
Oh, that wasn't...
that didn't work.

01:26.041 --> 01:27.361
That was...
not the right thing.

01:27.363 --> 01:28.683
- Wait, let's see it.
- Play it.

01:28.684 --> 01:30.877
- I think I got it right here.
- No...

01:30.879 --> 01:33.847
[Crowd cheering]

01:37.451 --> 01:39.452
Oh!

01:39.454 --> 01:41.821
Forgot about this.
[Laughter]

01:41.823 --> 01:43.256
[All clapping]

01:43.258 --> 01:44.557
That was not a fail.

01:44.559 --> 01:46.220
That was actually a serious accident

01:46.221 --> 01:48.061
that could've resulted
in severe bodily harm.

01:48.063 --> 01:50.343
All: - Fail, fail, fail.
- You're all failing right now.

01:50.344 --> 01:52.132
Congratulations on your epic fail

01:52.134 --> 01:54.267
of the use of the word fail.

01:54.269 --> 01:57.270
[Cheerful music]

02:01.833 --> 02:03.753
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

02:03.788 --> 02:05.645
[Alarm beeping]

02:05.647 --> 02:09.449
Oh, God.

02:09.451 --> 02:10.717
What's going on?

02:10.719 --> 02:12.819
Nothing, nothing is going on.
Keep moving, please.

02:12.821 --> 02:14.154
What's he measuring?

02:14.156 --> 02:16.289
Okay, excuse me, I'm the landlord.

02:16.291 --> 02:17.811
This is between me and the management,

02:17.812 --> 02:18.825
no one else, please.

02:18.827 --> 02:20.427
It's an EMF hotspot.

02:20.429 --> 02:21.828
[Gasps] Oh, my God!

02:21.830 --> 02:24.364
It stands for electromagnetic
fields generally caused

02:24.366 --> 02:26.666
by a concentration of wiring in one area,

02:26.668 --> 02:28.768
especially if poorly insulated.

02:28.770 --> 02:30.503
Dwight?

02:30.505 --> 02:33.740
Um, okay, I'm just walking into this.

02:33.742 --> 02:36.643
Am I to understand
there's a beehive in the wall?

02:36.645 --> 02:39.512
You think I have a machine
for measuring beehives?

02:39.514 --> 02:41.214
I was just asking a question, Toby.

02:41.216 --> 02:42.682
How are you not murdered every hour?

02:42.684 --> 02:45.885
Well, I'm not getting paid
to work in a microwave oven.

02:45.887 --> 02:49.689
Okay, listen,
everything here is up to code.

02:49.691 --> 02:52.392
Oh, the wires need insulation.

02:52.394 --> 02:55.762
It's a wire, people.
I'm not buying it a fur coat.

03:00.501 --> 03:01.835
- Thank you.
- You got it.

03:01.837 --> 03:05.138
Last week, I finally told Pam
about the other job

03:05.140 --> 03:07.307
- I took in Philly, the side job.
- Thank you.

03:07.309 --> 03:11.010
And she was so incredibly cool about it.

03:11.012 --> 03:15.115
And now, I just want to do
something huge for her.

03:15.117 --> 03:17.283
Like if we were in some biker bar,

03:17.285 --> 03:18.818
and she mouthed off to some bikers,

03:18.820 --> 03:21.721
and they came lumbering over,
and I was like, "wham!

03:21.723 --> 03:24.157
Gotta go through me first."

03:30.131 --> 03:32.165
[Knocks at door]

03:32.167 --> 03:33.666
Andy, could I have a word, please?

03:33.668 --> 03:35.268
Um, it won't take a moment.

03:35.270 --> 03:36.836
It's extremely important,

03:36.838 --> 03:38.872
and it really has to happen now.

03:38.874 --> 03:41.441
Fine, I will give you one minute...

03:41.443 --> 03:43.243
Oh, please, don't use the hourglass.

03:43.245 --> 03:45.412
You have one minute,
and your minute has begun,

03:45.414 --> 03:47.714
and no time will be added at the end,

03:47.716 --> 03:49.582
even to accommodate this sentence

03:49.584 --> 03:52.485
with all of its
baroque-dependent clauses

03:52.487 --> 03:56.489
and cascading turns of phrase.

03:56.491 --> 03:58.324
I'm trying to adopt a baby.

03:58.326 --> 04:01.694
A baby what?
A human?

04:01.696 --> 04:04.564
And the agency require character reference

04:04.566 --> 04:05.598
from my employer.

04:05.600 --> 04:06.933
Oh.

04:06.935 --> 04:08.168
You won't have to do anything.

04:08.170 --> 04:09.450
I would write the letter myself.

04:09.451 --> 04:11.271
You'd just need to sign it, so...

04:11.273 --> 04:17.043
Okay, and fall right into your
plagiarism-entrapment scheme?

04:17.045 --> 04:19.446
- I don't think so.
- It's not...

04:19.447 --> 04:22.282
And I happen to notice you're
down to about 30 seconds here.

04:22.284 --> 04:24.404
Well, then, if I could just
convince you that you...

04:24.405 --> 04:26.525
And those sand grains
are tumbling with fury down...

04:26.526 --> 04:28.555
It's not entrapment if I'm writing...

04:28.557 --> 04:29.923
Time's up!

04:29.925 --> 04:32.025
Fine.

04:32.027 --> 04:33.493
Sure, I'll read her letter,

04:33.495 --> 04:35.361
and if she tells the truth

04:35.363 --> 04:38.064
about how evil and unfit
to be a mother she is,

04:38.066 --> 04:40.300
then, yeah, I'll sign that.

04:40.302 --> 04:43.670
"Statistical correlations
exist between EMF radiation

04:43.672 --> 04:46.105
and various health hazards,

04:46.107 --> 04:49.409
but mainstream studies
are inconclusive."

04:49.411 --> 04:52.045
That means you can't make me do squat.

04:52.047 --> 04:53.046
You better fix this.

04:53.048 --> 04:54.280
I already ditched my uterus,

04:54.282 --> 04:56.182
and I ain't losing any more good parts.

04:56.184 --> 04:57.984
You people don't realize
what you're asking.

04:57.985 --> 04:59.652
I'd have to rip open the walls.

04:59.654 --> 05:03.056
I'd have to shut this place down
for a week.

05:03.058 --> 05:05.191
Week off.
That'd be great.

