contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:17.037 --> 05:18.917
Hey, if you don't want
to teach me PowerPoint,

05:18.918 --> 05:19.539
just say so.

05:19.541 --> 05:21.021
I don't want to teach you PowerPoint.

05:21.022 --> 05:22.942
Come on.
Just show me PowerPoint.

05:22.944 --> 05:25.111
- Just do the tutorial.
- You're the tutorial.

05:25.113 --> 05:27.714
No, dude, I'm not.
I'm not the tutorial.

05:27.716 --> 05:28.716
- You could be.
- Mm-mm.

05:28.717 --> 05:30.116
[Microwave beeping]

05:31.919 --> 05:33.353
What are you doing?

05:33.355 --> 05:35.021
Getting my wife a week off from work.

05:35.023 --> 05:37.090
You popped one kernel.

05:37.092 --> 05:41.327
Awesome, right?

05:41.329 --> 05:43.329
So creed is that dude's stepdad?

05:43.331 --> 05:45.331
Correct.

05:45.333 --> 05:48.501
Well, I don't know about the rest of you,

05:48.503 --> 05:51.204
but I'm just going to say it;
I'm nervous.

05:51.206 --> 05:53.206
I have no idea what health problems

05:53.208 --> 05:54.641
this is all going to cause.

05:54.643 --> 05:55.909
- He's right.
- What? Come on.

05:55.911 --> 05:57.471
I'm getting older.
I'm losing my hair.

05:57.473 --> 05:59.193
- I'm sorry.
- I'm gonna grow a third arm.

05:59.194 --> 06:00.613
I know what Jim is trying to do.

06:00.615 --> 06:01.975
He's trying to get big, bad Dwight

06:01.976 --> 06:03.650
to shell out for a huge repair job,

06:03.652 --> 06:05.885
while Lucky Jimbo gets a paid vacation.

06:05.887 --> 06:07.654
Well, sorry, Lucky Jimbo,

06:07.656 --> 06:10.023
I can live very happily
in a magnetic field.

06:10.025 --> 06:13.059
Most of my childhood heroes
got their powers that way.

06:13.061 --> 06:16.029
Side effects of EMF include headaches...

06:16.031 --> 06:17.463
Had them all my life.

06:17.465 --> 06:19.198
Breast pain...

06:19.200 --> 06:21.701
No nobbies, no probbies.
Nice try, Jim.

06:21.703 --> 06:23.269
Oof.
Infertility.

06:23.271 --> 06:27.340
[Scoffs] Yeah, right.

06:34.682 --> 06:38.117
Ah, there's my popcorn.
Can you just grab that for me?

06:38.119 --> 06:41.621
Keep your snacks on your side, Jim, idiot.

06:41.623 --> 06:45.425
- What the...?
- What?

06:45.427 --> 06:46.960
Some of these kernels have crowned.

06:46.962 --> 06:51.698
That's impossible
'cause that's a brand-new bag.

06:51.700 --> 06:54.534
Oh, my God.

06:56.337 --> 06:58.271
Andy!

07:01.609 --> 07:03.410
I'm going to drive you up to the lake,

07:03.411 --> 07:04.811
give you a whole week on the water,

07:04.813 --> 07:06.713
just you, me, and the kids.

07:06.715 --> 07:08.648
Oh, can we stop
by that pie stand on the way?

07:08.650 --> 07:11.484
You mean, "Laverne's Pies,
Tires Fixed Also"? Yes.

07:11.486 --> 07:13.606
We will be doing that,
and we'll be getting a dozen.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.647
A dozen different pies?
'Cause that means rhubarb.

07:15.648 --> 07:16.623
Why would you say that?

07:16.625 --> 07:18.091
I meant four apple, four blueberry,

07:18.093 --> 07:19.592
two cherry, one peach, one chocolate.

07:19.594 --> 07:21.027
I thought that was implied.

07:21.029 --> 07:22.462
Yeah, okay, then.
[Door opening]

07:22.464 --> 07:24.864
Ladies and gentlemen,
I have heard your complaints,

07:24.866 --> 07:26.933
and we reached a settlement.

07:26.935 --> 07:28.234
So...

07:28.236 --> 07:30.937
We will be leaving the office
for one whole week.

07:30.939 --> 07:32.472
Nice job.

07:32.474 --> 07:34.941
In my contract, it is stipulated

07:34.943 --> 07:36.976
that I provide a temporary work space.

07:36.978 --> 07:38.578
It will arrive in one hour.

07:38.580 --> 07:40.079
What?

07:40.081 --> 07:41.414
- What's this?
- Oh!

07:41.416 --> 07:43.282
- What?
- Bring it in.

07:43.284 --> 07:45.985
Roll into the future with work bus.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.621
Say good-bye
to wasteful buildings.

07:48.623 --> 07:49.922
These days, a mobile office

07:49.924 --> 07:51.958
isn't just for hotshot politicians.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.459
Now anyone can rent a work bus.

07:53.461 --> 07:54.927
If you've got a parking lot,

07:54.929 --> 07:57.864
a work space is just a phone call away.

07:57.866 --> 07:59.098
In this age

07:59.100 --> 08:01.300
of belt-tightening
and less-empowered workers,

08:01.302 --> 08:02.301
a work bus

08:02.303 --> 08:06.439
is how tomorrow gets things done.

08:10.092 --> 08:11.658
- Shh!
- Shh!

08:11.660 --> 08:12.692
Shh!
$23.99 a page, yes.

08:12.694 --> 08:14.527
- Six. Yes.
- Yeah.

08:14.529 --> 08:15.969
- [Screams]
- Oh, sorry about that.

08:15.970 --> 08:16.596
Oh, my God!

08:16.598 --> 08:18.431
Oops. Sorry.

08:18.433 --> 08:19.999
Lose weight.

08:20.001 --> 08:22.168
I'm trying.
Sorry.

08:24.839 --> 08:26.106
Ah.

08:26.108 --> 08:27.948
The Pennsylvania Department
of Public Welfare

08:27.949 --> 08:29.242
pre-adoption standard?

08:29.244 --> 08:31.845
Oh, of course, you were adopted.

08:31.847 --> 08:34.013
[Scoffs] I wish.

08:34.015 --> 08:37.417
No, I made some short lists,
I had a couple of sleepovers,

08:37.419 --> 08:40.587
but I never managed to get
in the end-zone.

08:40.589 --> 08:42.822
I don't know what it was.

08:42.823 --> 08:44.391
Not lovable, maybe?

08:44.393 --> 08:45.592
Oh, well.

08:45.594 --> 08:47.761
Listen, I'm really struggling
with this form.

08:47.763 --> 08:50.263
But as you know the system,
do you think maybe you could...

08:50.265 --> 08:52.532
Absolutely, I know exactly
what they want to hear.

08:52.534 --> 08:53.854
I would...
I would love to help.

08:53.855 --> 08:56.469
Oh, thank you so much.

08:56.471 --> 08:58.638
[Whispering]
Just don't tell Andy because...

08:58.640 --> 08:59.639
- He hates me.
- And...

08:59.641 --> 09:01.001
- Thinks I'm a monster.
- That...

09:01.002 --> 09:03.543
Should go back to Loch Ness.

09:03.545 --> 09:06.880
Stretch.
All right.

09:06.882 --> 09:09.616
How many times do you need
to take a stroll?

09:09.618 --> 09:13.086
I... my legs cramp up, okay?
It's a circulation issue.

09:13.088 --> 09:14.587
Boy, I will hammer-spank
your rear.

09:14.589 --> 09:16.156
All right, all right, gang.

09:16.158 --> 09:18.238
Let's just settle down.
You're yelling in her face.

09:18.239 --> 09:19.459
It's a medical thing.

09:19.461 --> 09:20.760
Just... You good?

09:20.762 --> 09:23.496
I'm good. I...
[Sighs]

09:23.498 --> 09:25.665
I'm so sorry for all of this.

09:25.667 --> 09:27.967
It's okay.

09:27.969 --> 09:31.137
You know what they say,
a change is as good as a rest.

09:31.139 --> 09:33.139
I... I need to get
to the paper, please.

09:33.141 --> 09:34.140
Sorry.

09:34.142 --> 09:35.275
Oh, God!

09:35.277 --> 09:36.576
- Oh, oh, my God!
- Okay...

09:36.578 --> 09:38.077
- Oh!
- I'll get you a napkin.

09:38.079 --> 09:39.546
Can someone get napkins, please?

09:39.548 --> 09:41.714
You know what, it's fine.
It's fine, let me just...

09:41.716 --> 09:42.715
It's fine.

09:42.717 --> 09:46.152
Pam, I'm really sorry.
I just...

09:46.154 --> 09:48.154
I'm... I'm really sorry
about all that.

09:51.425 --> 09:53.193
Really?
Smirking?

09:53.195 --> 09:55.995
What can I say?
I love justice.

09:55.997 --> 09:58.398
You forced me to spend money
on needless repairs,

09:58.400 --> 10:00.433
and now you're locked in a prison bus,

10:00.435 --> 10:02.368
and your woman drips with beverage.

10:02.370 --> 10:04.610
Hey, Dwight, I was trying
to do something nice for Pam.

10:04.611 --> 10:06.473
Can you just help me out?

10:06.475 --> 10:08.675
Can we maybe take this thing somewhere,

10:08.677 --> 10:10.844
or do something to not make this
the worst day ever?

10:10.846 --> 10:13.813
It's not my responsibility
to solve your marriage problems

10:13.815 --> 10:17.183
by spending my money on gas.

10:18.519 --> 10:20.587
Andy!

10:20.589 --> 10:22.021
Yo!
Toonces.

10:22.023 --> 10:23.239
You're the boss.

10:23.240 --> 10:25.240
Don't you think we'd all be
a lot more productive

10:25.241 --> 10:26.361
if while we were doing work,

10:26.362 --> 10:27.162
we looked up and saw

10:27.163 --> 10:28.803
the best rural pie stand in Pennsylvania?

10:28.804 --> 10:31.231
Ooh, I know I'd be more productive.

10:31.233 --> 10:33.566
- As would I.
- No question.

10:33.568 --> 10:35.735
No! No!
This is a work bus.

10:35.737 --> 10:38.037
The wheels are for transporting
the work space

10:38.039 --> 10:39.572
to and from the work site.

10:39.574 --> 10:40.840
What are you talking about?

10:40.842 --> 10:43.443
You're not the boss, Andy is.
Andy?

10:43.445 --> 10:47.347
All: Pies, pies, pies,
pies, pies, pies.

10:47.349 --> 10:52.018
All right!
The fat people have spoken.

10:52.020 --> 10:54.254
Dwight, get this bus moving.

10:54.256 --> 10:57.056
[All cheering and clapping]

10:57.058 --> 11:00.627
Next stop, Laverne's Pies,
Tires Fixed Also.

11:00.629 --> 11:02.862
Oh, yes!

11:02.864 --> 11:03.944
[All cheering and clapping]

11:03.945 --> 11:06.799
Yeah, Jim!

11:06.801 --> 11:08.234
So it looks like this work bus

11:08.236 --> 11:10.937
was a pretty good idea after all, huh?

11:10.939 --> 11:12.872
Get your foot behind the yellow line.

11:12.874 --> 11:14.874
You got it.

11:14.876 --> 11:17.644
[Applause] Yeah, Jim!

11:27.054 --> 11:28.288
- Stop.
- Come back.

11:28.290 --> 11:29.956
- Too late.
- Mm.

